review_blob: On nitro at Opal Divines pours thick black with a creamy tan head that lasts. Sweet vanilla aroma. Flavor is pure chocolate. Good medium bodied feel on nitro.

Pours an opaque copper color with a very thin tan head that dissipates quickly. Brown sugar in the aroma, subtly. Smooth almost buttery mouth feel. Starts butterscotch that fades into hoppy bitterness.
beer_name: Independence Brewing Ten Anniversary Ale - Dry-Hopped Barleywine

review_blob: Roasty aroma, almost black, thick with a lasting thick light brown head that leaves lots of lace on the glass. Roasty and chocolate dominates with a slightly sweet finish.
Hazy yellow with a thin, lasting white head. Little to no aroma. Spicy, some clove, coriander and pepper. Slightly bitter finish. Very refreshing.
Spicy aroma, pours golden with a thick tan head. Peppery bitter start with a rich malty finish, not too sweet. On tap at Jet Rock in the PHL terminal B
beer_name: Great Lakes Rye of the Tiger

review_blob: Pours straw color and hazy soul a thin white head. Great tasting Pilsner with a grassy start, sweet taste, then a dry finish. Was not expecting such a good light beer at an airport bar!
Pours black with a chocolate brown head. Almost no aroma. Chocolate, toasted bread, and just a hint of coffee. Nice sweet finish
At Draught 55. White beer with no head. Aroma of celery. Nice tart beginning with a clean finish.
Opaque golden color with a white head and lace. Banana and citrus aroma. Good carbonation and light mouth feel. Starts very sweet with a hint of banana, then finishes dry.
Pours dark amber with a thin tan head. Malty aroma. Smooth mouth feel. Starts very malty like cereal then finishes with a slight bitterness.
Pours orange with a thin white head that dissipates. Leaves nice lace on the glass. Dank and not bitter with some citrus zest in the aftertaste.
Strong sweet fruity aroma. Hazy golden color with no head. Taste very much like Fresca.
Pours hazy white with a thick white head. Light citrus, lemony taste with some residual sweetness.

Pours golden amber with a thin white head. Slightly butterscotch aroma. Very sweet up front, with banana and butterscotch later, and a slightly bitter finish. Excellent sweet Belgian Tripel. On tap at Opal Divines Marina.
On tap at Opal Divines Marina. Light sweet citrus aroma. Pours clear straw color with a thin white head. Good variation. Flavors of Orange, coconut lime. Slightly bitter aftertaste. Good carbonation.
beer_name: Austin Beerworks Lotion in the Basket

review_blob: Sweet chocolate aroma. Pours black with a very thin tan head. Thin mouth feel. Sweet taste with a hint of mint. No bitter aftertaste. On nitro at Yard House Las Vegas LINQ.
Bright, clean IPA. Very subtle aroma, clear golden pour with a lasting white head. Very well balanced floral and bitter tastes. On tap at Pour House in Las Vegas.
Dark copper with lasting tan head. Very toasty flavor with lasting bitterness. I wouldnt call this an ipa solely from the taste, but its very enjoyable.
beer_name: Riverside Dont Worry Be Hoppy Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours amber-orange with a long lasting white head. Smooth hop profile, not excessive in any one hop. Not west coast bitter, no "C" hop flavors.
A big beer. Pours dark reddish brown with a lasting light tan head. Rich, malty, peaty flavor. Gets more flavorful as it warms up.

There was little aroma. Pours a medium dark brown, but not as dark as most porters. There wasnt much flavor except for a bitter finish. It wasnt smooth like most porters. There was some coffee notes while drinking this beer. It did have a nice long lasting white head.
Pours light, no aroma. Not too bitter, good flavoring and finishing. lasting white head.
Almost no aroma. Pours clear, copper colored with a thin light tan head which dissipates quickly. Lasting bitterness, but not too much... very dank and a little citrus comes through
beer_name: Fort Bend Phat DJ India Pale Ale

review_blob:
Light amber color, clear - not hazy - little to no head.
Very sweet, with some alcohol burn and a hint of apple or mint
On cask at the Draught House. Pours black with a thin head. Vanilla strong aroma. Starts with vanilla, chocolate and coffee followed by bitterness. Some alcohol burn.
beer_name: Ballast Point Victory at Sea - Devils Share

review_blob: On tap at the Pour House in Sacramento. Dark red pour with a light brown head. Starts with prune flavor and finishes with a nice hop bitterness.
Fits the Helles style well. Clear golden with no head. Clean bready flavor slightly sweet leaving no after taste
Pours black and thick with a thin brown head. Starts sweet and then the vanilla kicks in, followed by the chocolate bitters. Very nice!
Starts sweet with very subtle roasted cereal, and leaves almost no after taste. Opaque black with a brown head that quickly fades away.
Pours dark brown with a thick light tan head. Lots of lace on the glass. Very sweet like maple syrup but not as thick. Ends with a roasty, chocolatey flavor but the syrupy sweetness never goes away.
dark orange with little or no head and no lacing on the glass. Chardonnay comes through, with almost no hop bitterness.  is it old?
Starts with a very wet hop flavor, then sweet bread. Ends with a grassy note. Light straw color with a lasting white head.
Caramel, grass pours orange with a thin light tan head. Leaves some lace on the glass. Starts with a toasty caramel and leaves a bitter aftertaste that lingers, but not too long.

Smells of Beech wood. Golden color, with a thin white head; no lacing. 
Starts sweet, then a touch of sour apple. Finished with some orange flavor. Very nice and complex.
Light golden color with a thin white head that laces on the glass. Sweet and fruity with some bitterness at the end.
On draught at Flying Saucer Austin. Pours dark copper with a thin tan head. Citrus aroma. Starts with fruity tastes, then a little hopiness and bitterness.
More than a porter should be. Great chocolate taste, sweet with no hip or other bitter after taste. Light brown head leaves nicely on the glass. Has the mouth feel of a stout.
Pours dark black with a lasting light brown head. Starts sweet, then the coffee starts to come forward with some hop bitterness for good measure. Excellent stout mouth feel, well carbonated.
On tap at the Burp Castle. Even the aroma is of creme brulee. The first taste is sweet and creamy. Not very much subtlety here, it hits you in the face. Pours dark black with no head.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Very dark black with a tan head, good carbonation and medium mouth feel, starts milky sweet then adds chocolate, and later cereal-like qualities from the oats.
Opaque black with a lasting brown head. Dark chocolate aroma. smooth light mouth feel. Starts sweet with the cocoa tastes, then the hops kick in and leave a nice balanced bitterness.
Hazy yellow with a light, white head. Fruity overtones on a Belgian Wit base. Smooth mouth feel and lasting sweetness dominate.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Dark amber color, thin white head. Almost syrupy mouth feel. Starts sweet with a hint of pears. Then taste nutty, finishes slightly bitter.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Straw color with a lasting light tan head. Grassy or clover tastes. Touch of caramel at the end, but finishes bitter.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Spicy, a little like cider with a touch of herbal flavor but no aroma. Sweet, not bitter or sour.
Faint floral aroma. Dark copper color. Thin to no head. Malty but crisp, not heavy. The sugar leaves an almost minty aftertaste.
Dark chocolate with just a touch of roasted nuts. Lasting tan head. Just a tiny bit too sweet to be "perfect".
Sour and sweet at the same time. Dark cherry flavor and color. Distinct Iambic tartness. On tap at The Blue Nile.
Thin white head, caramel colored. Good carbonation, balanced hop bitterness with malty sweetness.

beer_brewer_name: The Traveler Beer Company (formerly House Of Shandy)
review_blob: Tastes like a Hefeweizen with the lemons already squeezed in. Hazy straw color, lasting thin white head.
